    <note>Zheng(1) Jianzhong [13376] According to Cai(1) Xiang's [1651] inscription for Jianzhong's son, Yu(3) [13377] (q.v.), Jianzhong earned the jinshi. But his grandson, Xie [13373], merely notes that he was fond of guests and entertained travelers from the four regions (presumably this was the real reason for the decline in family wealth). I assume that Xie is correct. CBD, 5, 3698.</note>
